Dalzell: Frederick (Fred) P. Dalzell of the Dalzell towing company, see
<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030431/1919-01-22/ed-1/seq-14/" rel="nofollow">The sun., January 22, 1919, Page 14</a>, col. 6, &quot;WALSH IN HOT TILT AT HARBOUR HEARING - Subterfuge, He Charges&quot;
<a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030214/1905-01-13/ed-1/seq-6/" rel="nofollow">New-York tribune., January 13, 1905, Page 6</a>, col. 2, &quot;AGAINST NEW LIFE SAVING RULES - Steamboat Navigation Organization's Protest to Secretary Metcalf&quot;

He is named Frank B. Dalzell in <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83030193/1916-05-11/ed-1/seq-7/" rel="nofollow">The evening world., May 11, 1916, Final Edition, Page 7</a>, col. 2, &quot;HARBOR TRAFFIC OPEN AS STRIKE NEARS END&quot;
